dcterms:description: MIMIC-III is an openly available dataset developed by the MIT Lab for Computational Physiology, comprising deidentified health data associated with roughly 60,000 intensive care unit (ICU) admissions. It includes demographics, vital signs, laboratory tests, medications, and more.

dcterms:description: The PhysioNet Computing in Cardiology Challenge 2019 provided datasets for early sepsis prediction that have led to various approaches to sepsis prediction including LSTM-based models, random forest classification, and gradient boosting methods.
dcterms:title: PhysioNet Computing in Cardiology Challenge 2019
